## 1. Missing `APP_ID` test

Your controller throws:

```java
IllegalArgumentException
```

but in `@WebMvcTest`, if your `GlobalExceptionHandler` is not loaded, the test fails with `ServletException`.

Add this import on the test:

```java
@Import(GlobalExceptionHandler.class)
```

So:

```java
@WebMvcTest(AuthController.class)
@AutoConfigureMockMvc(addFilters = false)
@Import(GlobalExceptionHandler.class)
class AuthControllerTest {
```

Import:

```java
import com.bnpp.pf.arthur.core.exception.GlobalExceptionHandler;
import org.springframework.context.annotation.Import;
```

## 2. Callback test

It says:

```text
Exception named "APP_ID header or appId query param is empty"
```

That means the callback request is somehow hitting `/auth/start`, not `/auth/callback`.

Check your test method. It should be exactly:

```java
mockMvc.perform(get("/auth/callback")
        .param("code", "auth-code")
        .param("state", "state-123"))
```

not:

```java
get("/auth/start")
```

Also your controller mapping shows:

```java
@GetMapping("/callback")
```

so full path is:

```text
/auth/callback
```

After these two changes, rerun the controller test.
